<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10736351-ashley"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1609899944i/10736351._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10736351-ashley">Ashley</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I heard in an interview once that Karin got death threats over killing Jeffery (I&apos;m pretty sure I&apos;m the only one who was happy to see that tool go) so<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I heard in an interview once that Karin got death threats over killing Jeffery (I'm pretty sure I'm the only one who was happy to see that tool go) so I don't think she'll leave Will to die alone miserably. Maybe it's just me, but I think Karin cares about Will just as much as we do. <br /><br />I'm tired of Angie too, but as far as "evil ex's" go, she's one of my favorites. I'd hate to see this series end, but I have fallen head over heels in love with her standalone novels. I don't know how it would be possible, but I wish there was a way to keep Andrea from Pieces of Her going. I'm totally renewing my Netflix account as soon as the Pieces of Her show comes out. <br /><br />Sorry...this is long and all over the place. I might be a little too excited for The Last Widow to come out ha. Plus I could talk about KS books all day :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
