    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2838873460" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2838873460" />
    <a title="Linda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9472704-linda"><img alt="Linda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1336837712p2/9472704.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2838873460?book_show_action=true">Dec 10, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Linda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Linda" href="/user/show/9472704-linda">Linda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9472704-linda?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9472704-linda?shelf=police-procedural">police-procedural</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/9472704-linda?shelf=mystery-thrillers">mystery-thrillers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2838873460" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12678075628874902777">Let&apos;s just say this......<br/><br/>Even if you have never read a Karin Slaughter novel before, don&apos;t be intimidated by the #9 in this series. Although I&apos;ve read books by this author before, I never dipped my toe into the Will Trent Series until now. And, fellow readers, I dove completely into the deepest part of this pool......holding my breath until the very end.<br/><br/>Karin Slaughter beckons us into this storyline with a warmly envisioned mother/daughter outting at the mall. Mother is keeping a watchful eye on</span>
  <span id="freeText12678075628874902777" style="display:none">Let's just say this......<br /><br />Even if you have never read a Karin Slaughter novel before, don't be intimidated by the #9 in this series. Although I've read books by this author before, I never dipped my toe into the Will Trent Series until now. And, fellow readers, I dove completely into the deepest part of this pool......holding my breath until the very end.<br /><br />Karin Slaughter beckons us into this storyline with a warmly envisioned mother/daughter outting at the mall. Mother is keeping a watchful eye on her daughter as daughter does the pre-teen whine for lip gloss at the beauty counter. Mom gives in and both of them walk out into the parking lot. Out of nowhere the mother is swept up and shoved into a speeding car leaving her daughter cowering behind their vehicle. Mom just happens to be a scientist working for the Centers for Disease Control in Georgia. A coincidence? Oh, not hardly.<br /><br />Then Slaughter switches gears to find Will Trent, investigator with the Georgia Bureau, and his partner, Dr. Sara Linton, medical examiner, chillin' out at her house. They're taking advantage of some down time. Doesn't last long......a horrendous explotion takes place not far away and the duo take off to check it out. But they're involved in a car accident on the way by some raunchy looking guys. Said raunchy looking guys grab Sara and take off. Even though wounded, Will sets off to track these guys down. And so it begins......<br /><br />Whether you're a Slaughter newbie or an experienced fan, The Last Widow will have you gripping these pages without letting up. There's no treading water here. Slaughter sees to it that you are totally engaged with just enough background info to keep the story moving along swimmingly. Sara's experiences involving these raunchy men will set the tone for a gotta know fever. Something wicked is going on in the foothills of Georgia. Will Sara live long enough to find out what exactly that is? <br /><br />A treasure of a read by the highly talented Karin Slaughter.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12678075628874902777" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


